metadata.name: Fractal Amoeba #609
metadata.description:
These Amoeba are moving based on mathematics fractal. These mysterious creatures fascinate us. We would lose track of time and keep looking at them.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [e] to update drawing
- Press [0] to increase drawing speed
- Press [9] to decrease drawing speed
- Press [s] to save the screen to a PNG file
- Press [1],[2],[3],[4] to set pixelDensity=1,2,3,4. When you save it, the save image is 1,2,3,4 times resolution.

Create with p5.js

metadata.name: Anarchy #39
metadata.description:
"Anarchy" aims to pay tribute to the Impressionist masters and explore the interplay between randomness and control. My goal was to capture the bold use of color and the fleeting nature of light and movement that is so characteristic of the Abstract Impressionist style. 

This piece uses a total of 12 color palettes, each one inspired by a different Impressionist painter. Some artists have two palette variations, while others only have one.

I wanted to create something that was unique and that would reflect my own visual emotions while also paying homage to the artists that inspire me. "Anarchy" is part of my exploration of the relationship between randomness and intention, and a celebration of the enduring legacy of the Impressionist masters.

Made by wandurz using p5.js 
January 2023

metadata.name: Laniakea #76
metadata.description:
This piece captures the mysterious beauty of the Laniakea Supercluster, the colossal cosmic structure that contains our Milky Way galaxy.

A deep black backdrop is scattered with shimmering stars, evoking a sense of endless space and awe-inspiring expanse. Winds of dark matter are captured in the mid-ground, representing the invisible force that drives the formation of the galaxies within the Supercluster.

The foreground features a small spiral galaxy, shining brightly against the backdrop of the universe, reminding us that we are an integral part of an unimaginably grand structure.
